      },
      "date": "2023-03-24 03:38:08.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1\n\nBuilds on my machine. That's one of the packages below. Why not add a dependency on bash-completion? Is there ever a downside to having it?\n\n timothy@debian-desktop:~/Programming/lustre-release/debs$ dpkg -I lustre-server-utils_2.15.54-114-g1aacdc9-1_amd64.deb\n new Debian package, version 2.0.\n  size 810016 bytes: control archive=6768 bytes.\n     368 bytes,    12 lines      conffiles            \n    1101 bytes,    24 lines      control              \n   15760 bytes,   225 lines      md5sums              \n      71 bytes,     2 lines      shlibs               \n      67 bytes,     2 lines      triggers             \n Package: lustre-server-utils\n Source: lustre\n Version: 2.15.54-114-g1aacdc9-1\n Architecture: amd64\n Maintainer: Lustre Developers <lustre-devel@lists.lustre.org>\n Installed-Size: 2664\n Depends: libyaml-0-2, libselinux1, libsnmp-dev, zlib1g, libnl-genl-3-200, libmount1, libmount-dev, libkeyutils1, libkeyutils-dev, libgssapi-krb5-2, libkrb5-3, libssl1.1 | libssl3\n Recommends: perl, python3\n Suggests: bash-completion\n Conflicts: lustre-client-utils\n Replaces: lustre-client-utils\n Provides: lustre-client-utils (= 2.15.54-114-g1aacdc9-1), lustre-server-utils\n Section: utils\n Priority: optional\n Homepage: https://wiki.whamcloud.com/\n Description: Userspace utilities for the Lustre filesystem (server)\n  Lustre is a scalable, secure, robust, highly-available cluster file system.\n  This release is maintained by Whamcloud and available from\n  https://wiki.whamcloud.com/\n  .\n  This package provides a number of userspace utilities for\n  accessing and maintaining Lustre filesystems from a server.\n  If you only need to access the filesystem hosted on remote\n  servers, the lustre-client-utils package may be used instead.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
